About
Balneario El Escambron is a little beach, just to the east of Old San Juan. It is a family-friendly beach, with a small crescent of clean sand and usually calm waters, thanks to the coral reef a short distance from the beach.
Duration: More than 3 hours

    This beach is lovely, relatively clean and has proper facilities as well (multiple clean restrooms), a washing station, etc... There is paid parking available as well.   • R F
    13 contributions
    Beautiful, clean beach just a short Uber ride from the cruise port. Highly recommend!
    We were visiting San Juan on a cruise ship and decided to check out this beach after reading other reviews. It was fabulous! We took an Uber from the cruise port that was around nine dollars and got there in about 10 to 15 minutes. There were showers, bathrooms and we rented a chaise lounge and an umbrella for $15. They took cash, PayPal, or credit cards. It was a great place to swim and relax. Crystal clear water and because of the break wall of rocks, it was very calm. The beach was clean, no seaweed. The bathrooms were clean and there were a couple of food trucks, selling ice cream drinks, snacks, and even some beach products. There were lifeguards, and it felt very safe and a great way to spend the day. There is a Walgreens directly across from the cruise port, so we went in there, and grabbed some sodas, bottled water and snacks to take with us. A really fun, family friendly place to spend a day.
    Visited March 2024
    Traveled as a couple
    Written March 20, 2024
